def chart_regression(pred,y,sort=True):
  t = pd.DataFrame({'pred' : pred, 'y' : y.flatten()})
  if sort:
    t.sort_values(by=['y'],inplace=True)
  a = plt.plot(t['pred'].tolist(),label='prediction')
  b = plt.plot(t['y'].tolist(),label='expected')
  plt.ylabel('output')
  plt.legend()
  plt.show()
In [ ]:
def min_max_normalizing(data, column):
  min_value = data[column].min()
  max_value = data[column].max()
  data[column] = (data[column] - min_value) / (max_value - min_value)

Remove outliers¶

In [ ]:
Q1 = merged_df['Runned_Miles'].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = merged_df['Runned_Miles'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1
runned_lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
runned_upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

Q1 = merged_df['Price'].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = merged_df['Price'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1
price_lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
price_upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

outliers = (merged_df['Runned_Miles'] < runned_lower_bound) | (merged_df['Runned_Miles'] > runned_upper_bound) | (merged_df['Price'] < price_lower_bound) | (merged_df['Price'] > price_upper_bound)
cleaned_merged_df = merged_df[~outliers]
merged_df_1 = cleaned_merged_df.copy()

Images array preps¶

In [ ]:
images_output = []

# Iterate through the rows of the DataFrame
for _, row in merged_df_1.iterrows():
    input_images = []

    # Concatenate the path prefix and columns to get the full path of the image for each viewpoint
    for viewpoint in ['0', '90', '180', '270']:
        img_name_col = f'img_name_{viewpoint}'
        file_name = f"{row['brand']}$${row['model']}$${row['year']}$${row['color']}$${row['Genmodel_id']}$${row['adv_id']}$${row[img_name_col]}"
        img_path_col = f'/content/data/images/{row["brand"]}/{row["model"]}/{row["year"]}/{row["color"]}/{file_name}'

        # Load and resize images for each viewpoint
        image_temp = cv2.imread(img_path_col)
        image = cv2.resize(image_temp, (64, 64))
        input_images.append(image)

    # Create the output image by arranging the input images
    output_image = np.zeros((128, 128, 3), dtype="uint8")
    output_image[0:64, 0:64] = input_images[0]
    output_image[0:64, 64:128] = input_images[1]
    output_image[64:128, 64:128] = input_images[2]
    output_image[64:128, 0:64] = input_images[3]

    # Append the output image to the list
    images_output.append(output_image)

Fully Connected Neural Networks (only use table)¶

In [ ]:
checkpointer = ModelCheckpoint(filepath="./dnn/best_weights.hdf5", verbose=0, save_best_only=True) # save best model

for i in range(5):
    print(i)
    #
    visible1 = Input(shape=(x.shape[1],))
    x1 = Dense(200, activation='relu')(visible1)
    x1 = Dense(150, activation='relu')(x1)
    x1 = Dense(60, activation='relu')(x1)
    x1 = Dense(25, activation='relu')(x1)
    dense1 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(x1)

    output = Dense(1)(dense1)

    # hidden = Dense(128, activation='relu')(merge)
    # output = Dense(1)(dense14)

    model = Model(inputs=[visible1], outputs=output)
    model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
    monitor = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', min_delta=1e-3, patience=10, verbose=2, mode='auto')
    model.fit(x_train, y_train, validation_data=(x_test, y_test), callbacks=[monitor, checkpointer], verbose=2, epochs=1000)


print('Training finished...Loading the best model')

checkpointer = ModelCheckpoint(filepath="./dnncnn/best_weights_1.hdf5", verbose=0, save_best_only=True) # save best model

for i in range(5):
    print(i)
    #
    visible1 = Input(shape=(99,))
    dense11 = Dense(100, activation='relu')(visible1)
    dense12 = Dense(50, activation='relu')(dense11)
    dense13 = Dense(25, activation='relu')(dense12)
    dense14 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(dense13)

    #
    visible2 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    conv1 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible2)
    conv2 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(conv1)
    pool1 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(conv2)
    conv3 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(pool1)
    conv4 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(conv3)
    pool2 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(conv4)
    conv5 = Conv2D(128, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(pool2)
    conv6 = Conv2D(128, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(conv5)
    pool3 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(conv6)
    flat2 = Flatten()(pool3)

    #
    merge = concatenate([dense14, flat2])

    # hidden1 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(merge)
    # hidden2 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(hidden1)
    # output = Dense(1)(hidden2)

    hidden = Dense(128, activation='relu')(merge)
    output = Dense(1)(hidden)

    model = Model(inputs=[visible1, visible2], outputs=output)
    model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
    monitor = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', min_delta=1e-3, patience=10, verbose=2, mode='auto')
    model.fit([x_train, front_img_arr_train], y_train, validation_data=([x_test, front_img_arr_test], y_test), callbacks=[monitor,checkpointer], verbose=2, epochs=1000)

checkpointer = ModelCheckpoint(filepath="./dnncnn/best_weights.hdf5", verbose=0, save_best_only=True) # save best model

for i in range(5):
    print(i)
    #
    visible1 = Input(shape=(99,))
    dense11 = Dense(100, activation='relu')(visible1)
    dense12 = Dense(50, activation='relu')(dense11)
    dense13 = Dense(25, activation='relu')(dense12)
    dense14 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(dense13)

    #
    visible2 = Input(shape=(128, 128, 3))
    conv1 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible2)
    conv2 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(conv1)
    pool1 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(conv2)
    conv3 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(pool1)
    conv4 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(conv3)
    pool2 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(conv4)
    conv5 = Conv2D(128, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(pool2)
    conv6 = Conv2D(128, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(conv5)
    pool3 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(conv6)
    flat2 = Flatten()(pool3)

    #
    merge = concatenate([dense14, flat2])

    # hidden1 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(merge)
    # hidden2 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(hidden1)
    # output = Dense(1)(hidden2)

    hidden = Dense(128, activation='relu')(merge)
    output = Dense(1)(hidden)

    model = Model(inputs=[visible1, visible2], outputs=output)
    model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
    monitor = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', min_delta=1e-3, patience=10, verbose=2, mode='auto')
    model.fit([x_train, img_arr_train], y_train, validation_data=([x_test, img_arr_test], y_test), callbacks=[monitor,checkpointer], verbose=2, epochs=1000)

VGG-16 (front image only)¶

In [ ]:
vgg_model = VGG16(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(64, 64, 3))
In [ ]:
for layer in vgg_model.layers:
  layer.trainable = False
In [ ]:
checkpointer = ModelCheckpoint(filepath="./vgg/best_weights.hdf5", verbose=0, save_best_only=True) # save best model

for i in range(3):
    print(i)
    #
    visible1 = Input(shape=(99,))
    dense11 = Dense(100, activation='relu')(visible1)
    dense12 = Dense(50, activation='relu')(dense11)
    dense13 = Dense(25, activation='relu')(dense12)
    dense14 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(dense13)

    #
    vgg = vgg_model.output
    flat21 = Flatten()(vgg)
    dense21 = Dense(1024, activation='relu')(flat21)
    dense22 = Dense(256, activation='relu')(dense21)
    dropout21 = Dropout(0.2)(dense22)

    #
    merge = concatenate([dense14, dropout21])

    hidden = Dense(128, activation='relu')(merge)
    output = Dense(1)(hidden)

    model = Model(inputs=[visible1, vgg_model.input], outputs=output)
    model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
    monitor = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', min_delta=1e-3, patience=10, verbose=2, mode='auto')
    model.fit([x_train, front_img_arr_train], y_train, validation_data=([x_test, front_img_arr_test], y_test), callbacks=[monitor,checkpointer], verbose=2, epochs=1000)


print('Training finished...Loading the best model')
print()

VGG-16 (4 images)¶

In [ ]:
vgg_model = VGG16(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(128, 128, 3))
In [ ]:
for layer in vgg_model.layers:
  layer.trainable = False
In [ ]:
checkpointer = ModelCheckpoint(filepath="./vgg/best_weights.hdf5", verbose=0, save_best_only=True) # save best model

for i in range(3):
    print(i)
    #
    visible1 = Input(shape=(99,))
    dense11 = Dense(100, activation='relu')(visible1)
    dense12 = Dense(50, activation='relu')(dense11)
    dense13 = Dense(25, activation='relu')(dense12)
    dense14 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(dense13)

    #
    vgg = vgg_model.output
    flat21 = Flatten()(vgg)
    dense21 = Dense(1024, activation='relu')(flat21)
    dense22 = Dense(256, activation='relu')(dense21)
    dropout21 = Dropout(0.2)(dense22)

    #
    merge = concatenate([dense14, dropout21])

    hidden = Dense(128, activation='relu')(merge)
    output = Dense(1)(hidden)

    model = Model(inputs=[visible1, vgg_model.input], outputs=output)
    model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
    monitor = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', min_delta=1e-3, patience=10, verbose=2, mode='auto')
    model.fit([x_train, img_arr_train], y_train, validation_data=([x_test, img_arr_test], y_test), callbacks=[monitor,checkpointer], verbose=2, epochs=1000)


print('Training finished...Loading the best model')
print()
model.load_weights('vgg/best_weights.hdf5') # load weights from best model
model.summary()
